notes: 
1. no secured ENV variables used for testing purpose
2. on each app start for testing, database data is cleared, and empty tables are created.

SETUP AND RUN APP:

1. Set your postgreSQL database creds in "db/config.js" file
2. Start APP with: "npm install" and then "node index"

Upon successful startup, you should see the following messages in the console:
"Server listening on port 3000"
"Database connection has been established successfully."

RUN TESTS:
1. make sure server is running
2. command: "npm run test"

API documentation with swagger: http://localhost:3000/api-docs/

All provided requirements are completed and should work. 
For issues or questions, contact gegijaniashvili@gmail.com.
